# iNSSSO Implementation — Walkthrough

## What was built

Full implementation of the **iNSSSO algorithm** (improved Nondominated Sorting Simplified Swarm Optimization) for **Multi-Objective VRPTW** on Solomon benchmarks.

### Project Structure
```
g:\BaoCaoLuanVanThs\code\
├── core/                    # Problem & solution representation
│   ├── problem.py           # VRPTW loader (CSV + TXT)
│   ├── solution.py          # Random-key encoding/decoding
│   ├── objectives.py        # f1, f2, f3 objectives
│   └── constraints.py       # Capacity & time window checks
├── algorithm/               # Main algorithms
│   ├── nondominated.py      # Fast non-dominated sorting
│   ├── crowding.py          # Crowding distance + selection
│   ├── abs_search.py        # A*-Based Search local search
│   ├── nssso.py             # Base NSSSO
│   └── inssso.py            # Full iNSSSO (greedy init + ABS)
├── comparison/              # Comparison algorithms
│   ├── mopso.py, nsga2.py, moead.py, spea2.py
├── benchmark/               # Evaluation
│   ├── metrics.py           # Cov, IGD, HV, Nnds
│   └── runner.py            # Experiment orchestrator
├── visualization/           # Plotting
│   ├── pareto_plot.py, convergence_plot.py, route_visualizer.py
├── config/params.yaml       # Algorithm parameters
├── main.py                  # CLI entry point
└── venv/                    # Python virtual environment
```

